title: For Sale/Trade:  2003 badass crown vic police interceptor trade cash + guns
location: North. Baptist road, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent:
I am selling my 3 (4) owner 2003 Crown Victoria p71 police interceptor. This car was actually a detective car so there were no holes drilled for the spotlight, like most p71's this year. The first owner was the police station in Chicago, then it was moved to colorado by the third owner about 2 years ago i believe. Car has 155xxx on the odo and has no lights on the dash. Clean title. Runs strong just leaves some oil drips when its parked overnight. I have owned the car for about 6 months now and ive put roughly 8-10k miles on it. Im selling so i can get a 4wd, i miss my old one too much. Price is $7000obo which i believe is fair because you can strip the car and get near that much just in parts. Sound and aesthetics were done by second owner and performance mods were done by third owner. I have not upgraded the car since ive had it. Car has the 4.6l V8 motor.

Interior Upgrades:
Awesome pioneer touchscreen deck w/ CD, MP3, iPod hook up, navigation, AM/FM and can also play movies while driving ;)
Kicker 700 watt amp
2 10" subwoofers in custom made box. Im told it was the second owners hand-made box
2Kappa 2-way speakers 6x9
2 aftermarket tweeters in the front. Im sorry i do not know the brand but the sound quality is pretty amazing.
Full vehicle dynamat, so only you can hear and feel your music. Also the music can be up with no rattles inside or outside of the car. 
Practically new dvd player in the back, still has the screen protector. I believe its a 10-12" version, the nice one. Both players have been rigged to play the same thing if desired.
Car has custom gauges
Aftermarket tachometer, stock ones dont come with RPM gauge
"custom" cup holders/ tray. It was from another ford so it fits the rails but it doesnt fold conveniently into the dash like the stock Crown Vic's do.
Interior compass and temperature gauge thats from an older ford explorer but it is wired to work and it fits the interior seemlessly, you wouldnt be able to tell the difference.
6 seats and seatbelts, 3 in front, 3 in back. Very roomy and would have no issue fitting 6 people
LED lights instead of a dome light. 
Windows tinted, 20% in the rear and 35% in the front. 

Exterior/engine
20" Saleen premium black chrome rims. These were taken off a wrecked Saleen so they are a bit scuffed up but still in good cond. I had the front right one re welded in a spot because there was an expanding crack, no issues since then.
Premium drilled and slotted Brembo brakes, caliper and rotors. I can easily say that these brakes are some of the best out there. The crown vic weighs roughly 4400 lbs but these brakes make you feel like you are driving something that is hardly 1500 lbs. you can and will stop on a dime with these.
VERY bright HID headlamps
Custom LED lights replaced in taillights and parking lights
Has a very loud aftermarket horn
Tires are the worst part about the vehicle. Rear tires are worn and will need to be replaced before the weather gets cold again. The fronts are in decent shape but are mismatched treads. 
Chrome trim, shines up very nice. 
Mirrors have been modified to hold a blinker LED strip.
NOW, what makes this car unique. The EXHAUST. It has 3 exhaust settings, quietest, kinda loud and NASCAR loud. It is a dual exhaust with 4 exhaust tips, 2 for each pipe. However, right after the engine block electronic exhaust cutoffs have been installed and they make this car sound GOOD. I mean really good. Ive had a police officer comment on how good it sounded while he was giving me a ticket for speeding. Unfortunately these plates do tend to move around due to the vibrations the loud exhaust puts out. A plate on the passenger side fell off but i am having it re-welded as I type.
I am completely confident selling it while the part is welded because it doesnt hinder from the car or the experience, AT ALL. 

The car has other misc. things that im sure i forgot. Like the Viper alarm kit w/ remote start. Or the basics like power seats, windows, A/C is cold and heat is really hot. Engine has a K&N air filter. Hood is wrapped in carbon fiber, no bubbles, looks clean. Car comes with a 3 ring 1" binder full of service reciepts and even other previous owners paperwork that probably could have been taken out but i will just leave it as is for the new owner. If the car doesnt sell ill just keep it, id like a 4wd but if i get nothing but lowball offers i have no issue driving this for another year or across the country if i needed to. I can take any pictures you would like. The interior isnt clean yet but i will detail for a buyer. I have a husky/shepherd so there is an abundance of dog hair and would be very hard for me to keep continually clean until the car sold. Any questions you can feel free to email me, it goes through my phone so it will be answered in a timely manner. I am open to almost any offer, worst thing i can say is no thanks. Only trade i am open to is a trade +CASH. What do you have? Ill even take guns +cash, car+cash, cash+cash, you name it.
